The paper deals with action recognition using deep learning and computer vision techniques, which are typically covered under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of statistical moments and subspace descriptors is also related to the fields of multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of object and saliency detectors, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) applications.
